3. Types of Data We Handle
To provide our services via the Belle app and the
bellehealth.co
website, we handle three types of data, all of which are securely stored on servers in the European Union (EU).
Profile Data:
When you create a Belle account, we process some personal details such as a username and email address. The date of birth is not processed.
Interactivity Data:
For service provision and performance enhancement, we process data related to your interaction with our products. This includes device information (like device model, name, identifiers, settings, application identifier, crash data) that gives us insights about the device you use to engage with our app. We also collect browser information (such as settings, operating system, system settings) on our website. Additional interaction data includes the IP address provided by your browser or mobile device, needed to deliver the service to your device. For analytical, statistical, and regulatory compliance purposes in various countries, we use the IP address to identify your approximate location. However, we do not collect your exact location.
Health Data:
As a health app, we process health-related and other sensitive data that you opt to log in the Belle app. This may encompass details about your cycle (like period length), and depending upon the information you provide, it might also include other sensitive details about your symptoms. We only process the health data you decide to share with the Belle app via tracking. You have the option to use different methods offered by the app to log your health data in the app. This could involve manually inputting your data into the app or importing your data from other integrations or devices that Belle supports (like Apple Health or fitness trackers).
4. How and why we process your data
Processing of data is integral to the provision of Belle’s services. Each time our services are utilized, we gather, store, and analyze both personal and non-personal data through our own and additional third-party tools. Outlined below are the purposes behind our data processing activities, and the types of data we process in order to achieve these objectives:
4.1 To provide our services and understand your needs
In order to deliver our services, we process certain types of data:
Health Information:
Whenever you log your health details in the Belle app, either manually or using import integrations, we process this data. This allows us to provide our principal service as a health monitoring application. The data includes your cycle stats as well as other sensitive information that you decide to log in the Belle app.
Device Details, Event Data, Usage Info, IP Address:
We process this data when you interact with the Belle app or the
bellehealth.co
website. It helps us comprehend your engagement with our services and assists in improving technical performance.
Account Information:
We process this data when you create your Belle account on the app or website. This allows you to sign into the Belle app and enables us to communicate with you regarding service-related matters. These communications can include updates about your account, critical app updates, or suggestions and insights based on the health data you have logged. You can receive these communications through in-app messages, reminders, notifications, or emails.
Please read the following sections to understand which third party services, integrations, and partnerships we use to provide our core service.
4.1.1 Essential third party providers:
We use several third party providers to help us perform our core services.
Amazon Web Services
: Belle uses Amazon Web Services EMEA SARL (“AWS”) as our hosting provider to store our data on secure servers. We only use AWS data centers in the European Union. All data stored with AWS is encrypted by Belle.
Tally: Belle utilises Tally’s services for seamless data management and compliance. Tally is based in Belgium and complies with the GDPR framework. All form data managed through Tally is encrypted both in transit and at rest and is stored in Belgium, EU. Tally acts as a data processor on behalf of form creators, ensuring data security and privacy. We only share your information with our service providers who help us operate our business, in which case those third parties are required to comply with the GDPR framework (
Tally’s Privacy Policy
).
Sentry:
Belle employs Sentry for real-time error tracking, which enables us to identify and rectify issues promptly. Sentry is based in the United States and complies with GDPR by providing Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) for data transfer. Data processed through Sentry includes error logs and performance data, which are securely stored and managed to ensure the efficient functioning of our services .
Brevo (formerly Sendinblue):
Belle uses Brevo to streamline our marketing efforts, including email campaigns and customer engagement. Brevo is based in France and adheres to GDPR standards. All data processed through Brevo, such as email addresses and engagement metrics, is securely stored and encrypted. Brevo ensures data protection through measures such as secure data transfer and compliance with the EU-US Data Privacy Framework (
Brevo’s EU Privacy Policy
).
PayPal and Stripe (Course Payments):
When you pay for Belle Premenstrual Courses by credit card or PayPal, you authorize and give permission to Belle Health AI Technologies Ltd to charge your credit or debit card or account for the amount owed for payment of Belle Premenstrual Courses. When you purchase Belle Premenstrual Courses, your information (i.e. credit card and contact info) may be collected by the third-party merchants Stripe and PayPal (depending on the payment method you choose at checkout), who may have privacy policies or security practices that are different than ours. Belle Health AI Technologies Ltd is not responsible for the merchant’s independent policies or practices. (
PayPal’s UK Privacy Policy
,
Stripe’s EU Privacy Policy
)
4.1.2 Options for Account Creation
When setting up your Belle account for the first time, you have multiple registration options. Apart from using your email address, you can also leverage the services provided by Apple or Google.
Apple Sign In
: Belle employs the “Sign in with Apple” feature, granting users the ability to establish and access their Belle account using their Apple login details.
By choosing to register with Belle through Apple, Belle will exchange specific data with Apple, such as device data, IP address, and the information you initially provided to Apple upon account creation. This may involve transferring your personal data to Apple servers located outside the European Union. The choice to use the “Sign in with Apple” service and the degree of information you provide to Apple is entirely up to you. Note that no health data will be shared with Apple when using the “Sign in with Apple” service.
Google Sign In
: Belle offers the “Sign in with Google” feature, which allows users to set up and access their Belle account using their Google login details. If you choose this service, you authorize us to collect basic information from Google, like your email address. You can manage this at any time in your Google account. For more details on this, refer to
Google’s resources.
By opting to register with Belle through Google, Belle will exchange with Google the types of data you initially provided to Google when creating an account with them (such as name, email address). This might involve a transfer of your personal data to Google servers located outside the European Union. The choice to use the “Sign in with Google” service and the degree of information you provide to Google is entirely up to you. Note that no health data will be shared with Google.
4.1.5. Payment provider
If you decide to subscribe to Belle Premium via
t
he Belle app, your subscription will be handled by our payment providers. We use Apple Inc for payments made via the App Store and Google LLC for payments made via Google Play. In these cases, Apple Inc or Google LLC will become the controller of your payment data, while Belle will remain the controller for all the data related to the use of the Belle app. Neither Apple Inc nor Google LLC will have access to any of your tracked data or other app-related usage data. You can read more about how Apple Inc and Google LLC handle your payment data in their respective Privacy Policies:
Apple Privacy Policy
and
Google Privacy Policy
.
4.2 Provision of Customer Assistance
In the event that a Belle user reaches out to our Support Team with inquiries related to our offerings, we may interact with the user via email to offer customer assistance. This service is incorporated as a part of our premium Belle Plus subscription.
Should you avail of this service, Belle will need to access and process your personal data, including your health data, contingent on the specifics of your request. This is done so that we can provide you with the necessary support in response to your request.
Whenever data is transferred to providers operating outside of the European Economic Area (EEA), we ensure to implement appropriate safeguards as mandated by the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) (refer to Section 4).
Legal Basis:
The legal basis for processing your account data and usage data for customer assistance is Art 6 Sec. 1 lit b) GDPR, and Art 9 Sec.2 lit a) GDPR for your health data.
When you approach the Belle Support Team, you explicitly provide your consent for the processing of your personal data, including your health data, to enable us to respond to your inquiry.
We delete all personal data collected for our customer service once it is deemed unnecessary for the purpose for which it was originally gathered.
4.3 For Statistical, Analysis and Improvement Purposes
In order to improve the user experience on the Belle app, we process and scrutinize certain data for the purpose of refining the app and simplifying its features. This involves usage data such as your device ID and IP address.
Through the enhancement of the app and its technical infrastructure, we strive to provide an optimal experience for you and the broader Belle community. This enables us to customize the app for various device types and, above all, to ensure the highest quality app experience.
Third party providers:
For this purpose, we do not utilize any third-party providers.
Legal basis:
The processing of your usage data for the technical enhancement of the Belle app is founded on Art 6 Sec.1 lit f) GDPR. It is rooted in Belle’s legitimate company interest to continually refine the app and offer an improved service to you. We assume that you would have no objections to this. Nonetheless, you can always choose to opt out of this data processing at any time in your Belle app’s privacy settings by disabling:
I consent to anonymized processing for Statistical, Analysis and Improvement Purposes.
We delete all personal data gathered for the technical enhancement of the Belle app as soon as it is no longer needed for the purpose for which it was initially collected.
4.4 To improve bellehealth.co with Website Analytics
Generally, cookies serve to remember preferences, store details for elements like shopping carts, provide tracking data to third party applications like Google Analytics, or mark your device for specific advertising activities like retargeting.
Legal Ground:
Your usage data’s processing for website analytics is based on the consent you provide under Art 6 Sec.1 lit a) GDPR:
By visiting our website, you agree via an opt-in in the cookie banner that Belle can utilize cookies and third-party services, and accumulate your usage data under a unique identifier for purposes such as tracking, analyzing, enhancing our website, and for advertising purposes like displaying Belle content relevant to you.
The use of non-essential cookies on our website is based on consent according to the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018. You have the option to refuse the use of non-essential cookies through the pop-up notification when you visit our website. If you consent to the use of non-essential cookies, you can revoke your consent at any time in your browser’s cookie settings.
All personal data accumulated for analyzing our website is removed by us as soon as it is no longer required for the purpose it was initially collected for.
4.5 To deliver Belle Newsletters
In order to distribute newsletters and email updates, we process the contact information of individuals who have chosen to receive these communications.
For those who have signed up for Belle’s newsletter service without being a Belle app user, we will process the details provided during the registration on
bellehealth.co
. This can include your name and email address, which is used for sending the newsletters you’ve subscribed to.
For those who are Belle app users with an account, Belle will use the email address supplied during account registration to send newsletters and occasional promotional emails. The content of these emails could be related to Belle services you’re using, or could include promotions for third-party products from our partners that may be of interest to you.
Third parties:
To facilitate our newsletter services, Belle may share details like your email address with third-party service providers. Currently, we use the services of Brevo for this purpose. For more information about Brevo, see Section 4.1.1. Whenever data is sent outside of the United Kingdom or the European Economic Area (EEA), we ensure that the necessary safeguards in compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) are applied (see Section 4).
Legal basis:
The legal justification for sending our newsletter is your consent as per Art 6 Sec.1 lit a) GDPR. The legal basis for promotional emails is based on Art 6 Sec.1 lit a) and lit f) GDPR.
You have the option to unsubscribe from our newsletters or promotional emails at any time by clicking the unsubscribe link found at the end of the emails.
All personal data gathered for the purpose of delivering our newsletter services is erased by us once it is no longer needed for the purpose it was initially collected for.
5. Data transfer outside the UK or European Union
Any personal data collected from you may be transferred to countries outside the United Kingdom or the European Economic Area (EEA) only if we comply with applicable privacy regulations and ensure that your privacy rights are protected. This includes ensuring that all such transfers are subject to approved safeguards that meet the requirements of Data Protection Legislation, such as the use of EU Commission or UK ICO-approved Standard Contractual Clauses.
To ensure an adequate level of data protection in accordance with Article 46 of the GDPR, we have implemented Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) with all third-party data processors located outside the EEA and the UK, where there is no adequacy decision by the EU Commission for their country. For data processing by U.S.-based providers, we utilize third-party services certified under the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework, providing assurance under Article 46 of the GDPR.
6. Your Data Protection Rights
We believe that data privacy is a
basic human right
. At Belle we strive to ensure that your rights are respected.
Here are some key facts about your privacy that we would like you to know:
i. Our products and services have been designed to minimize the use of personal data. We only collect and process your data for the purposes outlined above and detailed in this Privacy Policy.
ii. Your data is highly secured on our servers (using the AWS DynamoDB database, which encrypts all of your data, as seen
here
to protect your data from unauthorized access). You can contact us at
trust@bellehealth.co
if you have any questions about the security of our services.
iii. We do not retain your personal data in an identifiable format for longer than necessary to deliver our services. As soon as we can, we encrypt your email address and create an anonymised user ID so that your health data is not directly connected to your email address on our systems.
iv. Belle does not engage in any automated decision-making or profiling activities.
As a user of the Belle’s services, you may exercise your rights under the UK and EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) to:
i. Request information on, or a copy of, your personal data processed by Belle. Upon your request, this information will be provided to you electronically. You can contact us to request your information at
trust@bellehealth.co
.
ii. Gain access to your personal data by requesting a backup of your data (as explained in the next section) in a format that is readable by other companies or organisations (data portability).
iii. Correct your personal and health data in the app settings and in the tracking categories available in the Belle app.
iv. Withdraw your consent from ongoing data processing at any time by deleting your account, and/or changing your privacy preferences in the Settings, and/or unsubscribing from our newsletter or other email communications by clicking the link at the bottom of the email or by contacting
trust@bellehealth.co
.
v. Request the complete deletion of your data, including all past data sent to third-party services used for tracking and analysis, by reaching out to
trust@bellehealth.co
. Your data will be deleted within 30 days.
vi. File a complaint with the relevant supervising authority (such as the UK Information Commissioner’s Office if you are based in the UK or if you are a resident of California, the California Privacy Protection Agency) if you believe Belle is processing your personal data under violation of applicable data protection regulations.
7. Procedures for Data Security
Ensuring the privacy of your data is a core principle at Belle. We implement security protocols to safeguard against inappropriate handling, loss, or changes to personal information under our control. Industry-standard procedures are followed for the transfer and storage of your data. While we cannot guarantee absolute immunity from misuse, loss or alteration of information, we exhaust all reasonable measures to prevent such occurrences. We cannot assure with absolute certainty that our security protocols will be impervious to unauthorized third-party breaches, leading to illicit access to our site or app and the content or information within.
7.1 How Belle Secures your Personal Data
When you create an account with Belle, your personal profile data is stored separately from your health data and your service settings. Doing this means your health data has an even higher level of protection. Belle uses servers located in the European Union to process and store your personal data.
When you create your Belle password, it’s stored using one-way encryption with both “hashing” and “salting” techniques. This means your password is combined with a random string of characters and then scrambled up so it’s unreadable. Not even Belle staff have access to your password. Doing this ensures extra protection for your password. Note that if you use social login to create your account, Belle does not receive your original password.
When your data is sent between your device and our Belle servers, we use hypertext transfer protocol secure (HTTPS). This is a type of encrypted data transmission, which scrambles the information being sent so it’s unreadable. Doing this increases the security of your data transfer. HTTPS is the same technology used to create secure connections for your web browser and is indicated by a padlock icon in the URL bar of your browser.
When you subscribe to Belle Premium, all your payment information is securely processed by the Apple App Store or Google Play Store. Belle does not store your payment information at any time.
7.2 Disclosure of Your Personal Data
We only share your personal data with third parties when necessary to provide our services, comply with legal requirements, for legitimate business interests, or with your explicit consent. Personal data may be shared under the following circumstances:
Third Party Service Providers: This includes technology service providers, payment processors, data storage providers, and marketing platforms.
Third Party Apps: Personal data may be shared with other apps only with your consent.
Legal Obligations: When required by law, regulation, or court order.
Law Enforcement Requests: In response to legitimate requests from law enforcement agencies.
Please note that as a UK company, we’re not required to have to comply with US criminal subpoenas requesting disclosure of data, in light of Roe v Wade.
Legal Advice and Litigation: To seek legal advice or in connection with litigation.
Business Transactions: In the event of a sale, purchase, or merger of our business.
7.3 Belle’s Recommendations for Protecting your Data
We believe the biggest threat to the security and privacy of your personal data is if someone, probably someone you know, gains access to any of your devices. The data you enter into Belle is private and it should stay that way.
We have outlined some ways to keep your devices secure below.
Protect your Belle Account:
Ensure you establish a distinctive and lengthy password for your Belle account. Utilizing a password manager for this task is highly recommended.
Protect your device:
i. Enable the security settings on your device such as PIN, TouchID (for iPhone 5S and later models), or FaceID (for iPhone X and onwards). This action ensures that your data on Belle is encrypted, and no unauthorized person can access your device.
ii. Initiate a feature that allows you to delete all the data from your device if it ever gets lost or stolen. For iOS users, you need to perform two steps to activate this feature: Firstly, you should enable “Find My iPhone” via iCloud. Here are the instructions on the
Apple Support pages
. Secondly, you should turn on the “Erase your device” option, and you can find the instructions on the
Apple Support pages
.
For Android users, you need to download and configure
Find My Device
(previously known as Android Device Manager) from the Google Play Store. If required, utilize the connected
web interface
to remotely lock or erase your phone.
8. Cookies on bellehealth.co
We use cookies on our
bellehealth.co
website to track performance and improve our services.
8.1 What is a Cookie?
Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help websites remember your activities and preferences, enhancing your browsing experience. Cookies are essential for functions like retaining preferences, storing shopping cart information, providing tracking data to third-party applications, and identifying your device for special advertising purposes such as retargeting.
8.2 Why do we use Cookies?
We utilize third-party analytics and tracking services to measure our website’s performance. When data is transferred outside of the United Kingdom or European Economic Area (EEA), we apply safeguards as required by the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) (see Section 4). We share minimal technical data with advertising networks to ensure you do not see Belle ads if you have already downloaded the app or subscribed to Belle Premium.
We obtain your consent before using any non-essential cookies on your device when you access our website. You may withdraw your consent at any time by disabling cookies on your device or by following the instructions to withdraw consent individually for each third-party provider Belle uses for tracking and analysis services.
8.3 Managing Cookies
You can disable cookies on Belle’s site by adjusting your browser settings. Here is a short guide to help you:
Internet Explorer (version 10):
Go to “Tools,” select “Internet Options,” click “Privacy,” and then “Advanced” to override cookie handling.
Firefox (version 24):
Go to “Tools,” select “Options,” click “Privacy,” choose “Use custom settings for history,” and untick “Accept cookies from sites.”
Chrome (version 29):
Access the “Customize and control” menu, select “Settings,” “Show advanced settings,” “Content settings,” and choose “Block sites from setting any data” under “Cookies.”
Blocking all cookies may negatively impact the usability of many websites, including ours. If you block cookies, you may not be able to use all the features on our website.
You can delete cookies already stored on your device by following these steps:
Internet Explorer (version 10):
Manually delete cookie files (instructions at
support.microsoft.com/kb/278835
).
Firefox (version 24):
Go to “Tools,” select “Options,” click “Privacy,” choose “Use custom settings for history,” click “Show Cookies,” and then “Remove All Cookies.”
Chrome (version 29):
Access the “Customize and control” menu, select “Settings,” “Show advanced settings,” “Clear browsing data,” and then “Delete cookies and other site and plug-in data.”
For more information about cookies and how to manage them, visit
www.aboutcookies.org
.
8.4 Third-Party Cookies
We use third-party services to track the performance of our services and improve Belle. These include:
Google Analytics:
Our website and mobile app use
Google Analytics
, an analysis service operated by Google Inc. Google Analytics uses cookies to allow for anonymous analysis of your website and app use and interactions, such as which screens you visit most in the Belle app, to personalize your experience and improve our services. Information produced via cookies is transferred to and stored on Google-operated servers in the USA. Google Analytics helps us recognize users, track navigation patterns, improve usability, analyze website and app usage, administer services, prevent fraud, and enhance security.
Google may transfer this information to third parties if required by law or if third parties process data on Google’s behalf. Google does not link your IP address to any other personal data. You can prevent cookies from being stored by changing your browser settings; however, this may affect your experience on our website or using our features.
By using Belle’s website, you consent to the use and processing of non-personal data by Google as described. You can withdraw your consent for this use of your data at any time, but this withdrawal applies only to future activities.
9. Young Users of Belle
Users in the United States must be at least 13 years old to use our services. In compliance with the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) of 1998, we do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will promptly delete the information and the associated account.
Users in the European Union (EU), European Economic Area (EEA), United Kingdom (UK), and Canada must be at least 16 years old to use our services, unless they have verifiable consent from a parent or legal guardian. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 16 without such consent. If we discover that a user under 16 is using our services without the necessary consent, we will take steps to delete the information and deactivate the account.
By registering for an account, you confirm that you meet the age requirements applicable in your country or have the necessary parental consent.
If you are a parent or guardian and find that your child is using our services without your approval, or if you have any questions about our data privacy practices, please contact us at
trust@bellehealth
. We are committed to addressing your concerns and protecting children’s privacy.
For any concerns related to data privacy or to report unauthorized use of our services by a child under the relevant age, please reach out to us at
trust@bellehealth
. We are dedicated to ensuring the privacy and safety of all our users.
10. Changes to this Privacy Policy
Belle reserves the right to amend this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in the law, our data collection and data use practices, the features of Belle’s services, or advances in technology.
Please check this page periodically for changes and refer to the “last updated” date at the top of the page to know if it has been revised since your last visit. If we make a change to this Privacy Policy that, in our sole discretion, is material, we will notify you by posting notice of these changes in this Privacy Policy.
11. Responsibility for Belle’s Data Processing
Belle is developed in London, United Kingdom, and our data handling aligns with the high standards enforced by UK and European Union legal requirements. Belle is developed by Belle Health AI Technologies Ltd, 71-75 Shelton Street, Covent Garden, London, United Kingdom, WC2H 9JQ. Additional contact information can be found
here
. Belle has a designated data protection officer. Feel free to reach out to
trust@bellehealth.co
if you have any queries.
12. The Governing Language of this Privacy Policy
Belle caters to a global audience, with members interacting with the Belle app in numerous languages. We engage professional translators and proofreaders to ensure the accurate translation of all our communications, including this Privacy Policy, into the various languages needed.
However, it’s important to note that while we strive for complete accuracy in all our translations, we cannot guarantee that they are 100% accurate, particularly when it comes to legal content. Consequently, the English version of this Privacy Policy is considered the original and prevailing version in the event of any discrepancy with the translated versions. The latest version of this Privacy Policy is always available in English on our website.
